{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-1-chapter-level-1-tsx","path":"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/have-i-got-the-right-topic/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"7676fe08-e0bb-533d-aaeb-0b6a165afc02","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","depth":1,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c5761d72-2693-4c9f-bd5e-aa0600b96a92 --><h1>Have I got the right topic?</h1><!-- end field c5761d72-2693-4c9f-bd5e-aa0600b96a92 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item efa72a9b-697d-4b28-944e-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field bd201b8b-834b-408f-a219-acbd00890989 --><p>From birth onwards.</p><!-- end field bd201b8b-834b-408f-a219-acbd00890989 --><!-- begin field aa2f284f-0c14-4b66-8a8a-aa0600b96a92 --><p>This CKS topic is largely based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidance <em>Healthcare-associated infections: prevention and control in primary and community care</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>], the NHS National Services Scotland (NHS NSS) <em>National Infection Prevention and Control Manual</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/references/\">NHS NSS, 2012</a>], the NHS England policy document <em>Standard infection control precautions: national hand hygiene and personal protective equipment polic</em>y [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/references/\">NHS England, 2019</a>], and guidance from Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust <em>Community infection prevention and control guidance for general practice: standard precautions </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/references/\">Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust, 2017a</a>].</p><p>This CKS topic covers the prevention and control of healthcare-associated infections in primary care.</p><p>This CKS topic does not cover the prevention and control of healthcare-associated infections in other care settings, including care homes or secondary care, or outbreaks of communicable diseases, or the management of diagnosed healthcare-associated infections.</p><p>There are separate CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gastroenteritis/\">Gastroenteritis</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/hepatitis-b/\">Hepatitis B</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/hepatitis-c/\">Hepatitis C</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/hiv-infection-aids/\">HIV infection and AIDS</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/\">MRSA in primary care</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/urinary-tract-infection-lower-men/\">Urinary tract infection (lower) - men</a>, and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/urinary-tract-infection-lower-women/\">Urinary tract infection (lower) - women</a>. </p><p>The target audience for this CKS topic is healthcare professionals working within the NHS in the UK, and providing first contact or primary healthcare.</p><!-- end field aa2f284f-0c14-4b66-8a8a-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- end item efa72a9b-697d-4b28-944e-aa0600b96a92 -->","topic":{"id":"6a4764db-67e6-5a98-ad6f-450c98a82a25","topicId":"97f6f71a-7aa5-40ec-8a1b-aa0600b96730","topicName":"Healthcare-associated infections","slug":"healthcare-associated-infections","lastRevised":"Last revised in May 2019","chapters":[{"id":"6d22e1d5-d924-5b35-8750-a68b353cf1c4","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"7676fe08-e0bb-533d-aaeb-0b6a165afc02","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ca5b248